name: Zach Conine
tweet: When we get through this pandemic (and we will get through it) the stories I want to read aren’t about the big sweeping programs.   I want us to remember people like @frcojmorales seeing a need and grinding out a victory for Nevadans desperate for help.   They’re the heroes.

name: Zach Conine
tweet: And one more thing.  The difference between $300 a week and $600 a week in additional unemployment, or between 11 & 16 weeks of addition help, is hundreds of millions of dollars into the NV economy.  It's the difference between families & businesses making it or not.  It matters.

name: Zach Conine
tweet: For instance, the most prominent source of 'small' business funding is PPP.  This program is an ineffective way of providing support to the types of businesses that NV's grant programs support.  Congress should pick up a phone and talk to a restaurant in Elko or NLV about PPP.

name: Zach Conine
tweet: Couldn't agree more, @GovSisolak.  There are wins in this stimulus package, including much needed rental assistance and an extension of unemployment benefits.  This package should have been passed in July; the pandemic has gotten worse and the needs have grown.

name: Zach Conine
tweet: This headline is irresponsible.  How about: “Nevada using a defined and expected mechanic, already being used by 22 other states, to borrow money from the Federal Government. Unemployment benefits will continue without interruption”.

name: Zach Conine
tweet: Proud to join with @Culinary226 in this fight to get Nevada renters and landlords the help that they need.   Our economic recovery is on the line.

name: Zach Conine
tweet: I’d be remiss if I didn’t thank @ClarkCountyNV for their continuous evolution of the program and the dozens of landlords who have reached out for help because they wanted to help their tenants.

name: Zach Conine
tweet: We know landlords need help; which is why we’ve continually revised the CHAP program to make it easier to get funds.  Additionally, if you’re a small landlord and your lender isn’t helping you out, let me know and I’ll call them with you. We’re all in this together.

name: Zach Conine
tweet: @SteveSebelius @tsegerblom Luckily, a majority of Nevada homeowners are already covered by the FHA moratorium, dozens of landlords are receiving PETS dollars and we’ve helped dozens more talk to their banks about avoiding foreclosure.  When in doubt, send them to your friendly neighborhood Treasurer.
